channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden, Harris head to hurricane-ravaged Southeast in wake of Trump visit
item.description: President Biden and Vice President Harris each travel to the storm-ravaged Southeast on Wednesday, two days after Donald Trump visited – as the death toll and devastation from Hurricane Helene soars.

item.title: Justices ready to hear cases on protecting minors for new term, await possible election disputes
item.description: The Supreme Court has teed up a series of disputes addressing health and safety issues for minors for its upcoming term, which kicks off Monday.

item.title: Iran’s Ballistic-Missile Attack Is a Failure of Democratic Appeasement
item.description: For 15 years, Obama-Biden-Harris have coddled the radical Islamic regime and made war more likely.

item.title: From Iran To Illegal Immigration, Here Are Tim Walz’s Biggest Lies From The Debate
item.description: Gov. Tim Walz told lies on wide-ranging topics while debating Sen. J.D. Vance.

item.title: Vance addresses previous criticism of Trump: 'I was wrong about Donald Trump'
item.description: Republican Sen. JD Vance of Ohio said he was "wrong about Donald Trump" in the past. only coming around after the former president "delivered for the American people."

item.title: Vance, Walz battle over border, economy, abortion in election's final debate
item.description: In what is likely to be the final debate of the 2024 election, Sen. J.D. Vance and Gov. Tim Walz engaged in a proxy fight on behalf of Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump on the top issues voters say they care about five weeks from the election.

item.title: Populists in power, &c.
item.description: On Mexico, Japan, Hezbollah, China, Eric Adams, Donald Trump, a perfect game in football, and more.

item.title: No, Endorsing Kamala Harris For President Isn’t What Jesus Would Do
item.description: Christians should reject the backward theology of teachers who twist the character of Christ to punish their political enemies.

item.title: Voters react to JD Vance claiming he and Donald Trump support 'clean air, clean water'
item.description: JD Vance said at the CBS Vice Presidential Debate that he and Donald Trump support "clean air, clean water," prompting mixed reactions from voters.

item.title: Winners and losers in the vice presidential debate
item.description: Here are the winners and losers in Tuesday's vice presidential debate.

item.title: The SEC Joins the Regulatory Attack on Fossil Fuels
item.description: The unintended market consequences of SEC-promoted decarbonization will be profound.

item.title: Vance Calls Out Democrats’ First Amendment Crackdown: ‘Harris Is Engaged In Censorship On An Industrial Scale’
item.description: The Republican vice presidential hopeful slammed his Democrat opponents for trying to rig the election by cracking down on Americans' free speech.

item.title: Voters react to Gov Tim Walz dodging Tiananmen Square question: 'I'm a knucklehead at times'
item.description: A focus group of voters were skeptical of Gov. Tim Walz's explanation for falsely claiming to have been in Hong Kong during the Tiananmen Square massacre.

item.title: Vance blames illegal immigration for rising housing costs
item.description: Sen. J.D. Vance said Tuesday that illegal immigrants are competing with Americans for housing and contributing to the soaring prices that have chased many people out of the dream of home ownership.

item.title: Destroying America from Inside the Movies
item.description: The Damned is a Trojan horse critique of modern America.

item.title: Vance KOs Walz, Harris, And Media On Illegal Immigration Spin
item.description: Trump's running mate not only took it to Vice President Kamala Harris and her No. 2, but to the Dem-friendly CBS News moderators.

item.title: Several questions about Walz's record not asked about during vice presidential debate
item.description: Several controversial moments from Gov. Tim Walz's past were not mentioned during the first and only vice presidential debate on Tuesday night in New York City.

item.title: Vance gets personal about abortion on debate stage
item.description: Sen. J.D. Vance got personal when discussing abortion on the debate stage Tuesday night, admitting that he knows someone "dear" to him who has had an abortion.

item.title: J. D. Vance’s Big Night
item.description: The Ohio senator won on substance as well as style.

item.title: As Appalachians Languish, CBS Moderators Minimize Deadly Hurricane Helene With Climate Change Question
